commit.message: Add `@since` annotations to functions added in 2.1.0.0

Remove modules from the deprecated 1.x api

We kept backwards compat long enough by now

Add the (&) helper class

This is so that one can easily require more than one constraint
when using bmapC, etc.
Add flipped-argument versions of traverse-style functions
Add FunctorT and DistributiveT instances for AccumT
Add FlexibleContexts to tests to make them compile on ghc 9.2
Change the category to commonly used "Data Structure"
Use ghc 9 by default in stack

Use Data.Kind.Type instead of *

Since * is being deprecated in ghc 9

Add a stack.yaml for ghc-9.0.1

Although stack doesn't currently support ghc 9,
and buliding crashes with a `Prelude.chr: bad argument: ...`

Fix Constraints{B,T} deriviation for proper bi-barbies

Valid instances were not being derived

Add a shell.nix and gitignore .envrc

I use `use nix` as .envrc to get `stack` in scope. But rather not
check it in to avoid conflicting with other people set-ups.
